283
00:15:01,567 --> 00:15:03,536
♪

284
00:15:03,536 --> 00:15:05,338
So you were the one
who turned the Baddies

285
00:15:05,338 --> 00:15:07,073
into lost disks.

286
00:15:07,073 --> 00:15:09,609
♪

287
00:15:09,609 --> 00:15:12,011
Aw, cut it out,
you're soaking me.

288
00:15:12,011 --> 00:15:14,080
♪

289
00:15:14,080 --> 00:15:17,417
Aw, Baku, thanks for
saving us from the monsters.

290
00:15:17,417 --> 00:15:33,966
♪

291
00:15:33,966 --> 00:15:36,436
Baku!

292
00:15:36,436 --> 00:15:38,671
Baku, Baku!

293
00:15:38,671 --> 00:15:40,740
♪

294
00:15:40,740 --> 00:15:44,510
So, you were the one
wiping out my troops.

295
00:15:44,510 --> 00:15:47,980
♪

296
00:15:47,980 --> 00:15:48,981
Huh?

297
00:15:48,981 --> 00:15:52,251
♪

298
00:15:52,251 --> 00:15:54,253
(laughs maniacally)

299
00:15:54,253 --> 00:16:21,347
♪

300
00:16:21,347 --> 00:16:24,116
So you survived
the fall from the cliff.

301
00:16:24,116 --> 00:16:25,685
This time I'll finish you off

302
00:16:25,685 --> 00:16:27,820
just like I did
with your master.

303
00:16:27,820 --> 00:16:29,455
Master?

304
00:16:29,455 --> 00:16:30,656
Get him!

305
00:16:30,656 --> 00:16:32,758
♪

306
00:16:32,758 --> 00:16:35,228
Oh, Baku!

307
00:16:35,228 --> 00:16:36,229
(snarls)

308
00:16:36,229 --> 00:16:37,463
Baku!

309
00:16:37,463 --> 00:16:58,985
♪

310
00:16:58,985 --> 00:17:00,353
Get off me!

311
00:17:00,353 --> 00:17:03,189
♪

312
00:17:03,189 --> 00:17:04,457
I've had enough of you.

313
00:17:04,457 --> 00:17:05,558
No!

314
00:17:05,558 --> 00:17:10,563
♪

315
00:17:10,563 --> 00:17:13,132
This time I finish you off.

316
00:17:13,132 --> 00:17:25,978
♪

317
00:17:25,978 --> 00:17:27,513
Baku!

318
00:17:27,513 --> 00:17:53,739
♪

319
00:17:53,739 --> 00:17:57,143
Hey boy, are you all right?

320
00:17:57,143 --> 00:17:59,445
Are you, boy?

321
00:17:59,445 --> 00:18:00,680
Baku.

322
00:18:00,680 --> 00:18:04,150
♪

323
00:18:04,150 --> 00:18:06,385
Where are you going, boy?

324
00:18:06,385 --> 00:18:07,787
What's in there?

325
00:18:07,787 --> 00:18:09,589
Hey, Baku?

326
00:18:09,589 --> 00:18:30,576
♪

327
00:18:30,576 --> 00:18:31,577
Huh?

328
00:18:31,577 --> 00:18:34,647
♪

329
00:18:34,647 --> 00:18:36,349
That boy.

330
00:18:36,349 --> 00:18:44,523
♪

331
00:18:44,523 --> 00:18:47,994
Poor Baku, the Baddies
killed your family.

332
00:18:47,994 --> 00:18:49,996
♪

333
00:18:49,996 --> 00:18:51,130
Baku!

334
00:18:51,130 --> 00:18:52,498
‐Genki!
‐'chi!

335
00:18:52,498 --> 00:18:53,866
♪

336
00:18:53,866 --> 00:18:57,803
Baku, hang on, boy, please!

337
00:18:57,803 --> 00:18:59,205
Baku!

338
00:18:59,205 --> 00:19:03,175
♪

339
00:19:03,175 --> 00:19:04,810
(giggling)

340
00:19:04,810 --> 00:19:06,045
Baku!

341
00:19:06,045 --> 00:19:08,614
♪

342
00:19:08,614 --> 00:19:10,082
Come on, boy!

343
00:19:10,082 --> 00:19:11,250
(Baku barking)

344
00:19:11,250 --> 00:19:14,420
♪

345
00:19:14,420 --> 00:19:17,323
That tickles!

346
00:19:17,323 --> 00:19:18,924
Baku!

347
00:19:21,494 --> 00:19:22,528
Huh?

348
00:19:22,528 --> 00:19:34,373
♪

349
00:19:34,373 --> 00:19:36,275
(crying)

350
00:19:37,910 --> 00:19:39,879
The villagers
probably made a living

351
00:19:39,879 --> 00:19:42,214
digging up mystery disks.

352
00:19:42,214 --> 00:19:44,216
And that's why
they were attacked,

353
00:19:44,216 --> 00:19:45,985
just like my village was.

354
00:19:45,985 --> 00:19:48,621
♪

355
00:19:48,621 --> 00:19:50,623
Even though the whole
village was destroyed

356
00:19:50,623 --> 00:19:52,458
and his master was gone,

357
00:19:52,458 --> 00:19:55,127
Baku stayed behind
to protect the forest.

358
00:19:55,127 --> 00:19:57,463
He protected us too.

359
00:19:57,463 --> 00:19:59,632
Go.

360
00:19:59,632 --> 00:20:00,966
Genki?

361
00:20:00,966 --> 00:20:02,101
♪

362
00:20:02,101 --> 00:20:04,203
We mustn't forget
that Baku gave his life

363
00:20:04,203 --> 00:20:05,905
so he could protect ours.

364
00:20:05,905 --> 00:20:08,407
We have to find
the Phoenix for his sake.

365
00:20:08,407 --> 00:20:13,179
♪

366
00:20:13,179 --> 00:20:16,348
Yeah, let's go
find that Phoenix!

367
00:20:16,348 --> 00:20:17,616
‐'chi!
‐Yeah!

368
00:20:17,616 --> 00:20:25,591
♪

369
00:20:25,591 --> 00:20:27,860
Goodbye, Baku.

370
00:20:27,860 --> 00:20:31,297
♪

371
00:20:31,297 --> 00:20:32,765
Come on!

372
00:20:32,765 --> 00:20:34,567
Genki, wait for me!

373
00:20:34,567 --> 00:20:35,568
'chi!

374
00:20:35,568 --> 00:20:46,612
♪

375
00:20:47,813 --> 00:20:49,048
♪ Monsters ♪

376
00:20:49,048 --> 00:20:50,716
♪ Monsters rule ♪

377
00:20:50,716 --> 00:21:15,241
♪

378
00:21:15,241 --> 00:21:17,309
♪ Monsters rule ♪

